<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 94 / Halifax increases its fixed rates
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Halifax, the UK's largest building society, yesterday lifted its fixed-rate
mortgages by up to 0.75 of a percentage point.
Its benchmark five-year fixed rate for new borrowers and existing customers
who are moving home is now 8.49 per cent, up from 7.75 per cent, while for
existing customers who are remortgaging, the five-year rate is 8.85 per
cent, up from 8.1 per cent. The variable rate has been 7.64 per cent since
December.
Mr Mike Blackburn, Halifax chief executive, said the range of discounts
offered by the society on its variable rate meant customers had a wide
choice of options 'at a time when fixed rates are hardening'.
