<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 94 / Philips wins cable contract
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BROWN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Philips, the Dutch electronics group, has won an ADollars 160m contract from
Telecom Australia to act as systems integrator for a new fibre-optic and
coaxial cable network it describes as a 'digital information superhighway,'
writes David Brown from Amsterdam. The contract forms the first part of a
ADollars 710m project, which will involve laying 10,000km of cable to 1.1m
urban homes in Australia to deliver 67 pay TV channels in 1996.
</TEXT>
