FT  09 APR 94 / Food and Drink: More bargains from Australia - Appetisers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JANCIS ROBINSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Majestic Wine warehouses have some significant reductions on Australian
wines this month - notably Cape Mentelle Cabernet Merlot 1991 for just
Pounds 6.99, the red wine expression of the man behind Cloudy Bay, from
fruit long-ripened on the south western tip of Australia.
Bibendum wine merchants meanwhile (071-722-5577) has a keenly priced range
from Victoria under the Red Cliffs label. Best buy is the Coonawarra
Cabernet 1991 at Pounds 4.99, although probably even better value for the
sheer quality, subtlety and potential is their Cabernet-based Yeringberg
1990 at Pounds 13.75 a bottle. This historic Yarra Valley winery has never
performed better.
*****
It might be snowing this month in England but why not at least toast the
prospect of warmer days? A good value choice is Bright Brothers Sauvignon
Blanc 1993 made from fully ripe grapes grown on an estate in Portugal's
Ribatejo by Australian Peter Bright. It will be in 170 Sainsbury's stores by
April 11 and, at Pounds 3.39, is a steal.
*****
Scottish Food Proms takes place in Glasgow from April 18-25. It begins with
a gala dinner for 250 but then widens its scope to take in chef talks,
demonstrations and the launch of the Scottish Food Education Project in
which over 40 Scottish schools will be taking part.
Among the Scottish chefs taking place will be David Wilson from the Peat
Inn, Nick Nairn from the Braeval Old Mill and John Webber from Kinnaird
House. For details contact: The Ideas Bank, Glasgow, tel: 041-636 6332; fax:
041-636-6335.
