<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: The BES and tax
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Could you please give some information on the effect of payments under
approved BES on total income for tax purposes.
1. If the relief given for BES payments in Paye coding reduces the tax
liability to the 20 per cent band, is it possible to claim relief on the
unused part of this band (eg, against building society interest taxed at 25
per cent).
2. Do payments under BES reduce total income so that, where appropriate, the
various age reliefs may be claimed?
1: Yes. 2: No. Ask your tax office for the free pamphlets IR51 (Business
expansion scheme) and IR121 (Income tax and pensioners). IR51 is obsolete
but might still be available.
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All enquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
