</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK house prices rose fractionally last month according to Halifax, the
largest building society. They increased by 0.2 per cent on a seasonally
adjusted basis in March compared to February - the third monthly increase
running. Nationwide, the second largest society last week reported a higher
monthly increase of 0.6 per cent. Over the past year, house prices have
risen by 2.6 per cent and the average house now costs Pounds 63,122,
according to Halifax which predicts that prices will be up by 5 per cent
over 1994.
