<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 94 / UK Company News: Willis Corroon in Australian purchase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Willis Corroon, the insurance broker, is to acquire Australia's largest
independent risk management company, Richard Oliver International. The UK
group could ultimately pay Pounds 17m to acquire full control of Richard
Oliver, which it will merge with its local broking subsidiary, Willis
Corroon Holdings.
Willis will initially acquire 40 per cent of ROI's issued share capital for
ADollars 4.5m in cash. Willis may purchase the remaining 60 per cent of the
risk management group under put and call options subject to the approval of
the Australian statutory authorities.
The consideration for this second part of the deal will be calculated on an
earnings-related formula subject to a maximum of ADollars 35m (Pounds 17m)
and a minimum of ADollars 10m (Pounds 4.85m), both figures inclusive of the
initial payment of ADollars 4.5m, with the consideration to be paid in
either cash or shares.
