<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 94 / UK Company News: United Breweries shares fall
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GRAHAM DELLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares of United Breweries dropped 2 1/2 p to 5p yesterday after the
lossmaking regional brewer and pub operator said it was in breach of its
banking covenants.
The statement followed completion of a valuation of its public house estate,
which showed a decline of some Pounds 7.2m and resulted in a sizeable
diminution in net tangible assets and the elimination of distributable
reserves.
The USM-traded group said that talks with its bankers, first announced in
February, were continuing.
Directors said proposals for a 'major financial restructuring and
acquisitions essential to improve critical mass,' probably including an
equity fund raising exercise, would be presented to shareholders in
approximately two months.
In a move designed to 'strengthen management resources' Mr Stephen Lambert
has been appointed as financial director.
Mr Michael Roberts and Mr David Ford, the property director, have resigned
from the board, although Mr Roberts will remain in a full-time capacity for
the time being to assist in the restructuring programme.
</TEXT>
