<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 94 / UK Company News: Blue Circle to convert bond issue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Blue Circle Industries, the cement maker, is to convert all of its Pounds
90m 10.5 per cent convertible capital bonds 2005 into preference shares
which will then be redeemed.
Each outstanding unconverted bond will be converted on June 21 1994 into one
preference share. Interest will be paid from December 31 1993 up to but
excluding the required redemption date.
The preference shares will be redeemed at their paid-up value.
Bondholders remain entitled to exercise their rights and to convert the
bonds and exchange the resulting preference shares for ordinary Blue Circle
shares.
This would be at the exchange price of 260p per ordinary share at any time
up to and including June 14 1994.
