FT  09 APR 94 / UK Company News: Institutions acquire Spring Ram stake sold
by US investor
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Lazard Freres Asset Management, the US investment group, has sold its 6.5
per cent stake in Spring Ram, the kitchens and bathrooms group, with De
Zoete &amp; Bevan, the brokers, buying and placing the shares.
The new owners are largely UK institutions. Spring Ram said it was pleased
that the shares had been 'placed with long term institutions who know us
well'.
De Zoete, part of Barclays de Zoete Wedd, bought 34.2m shares, comprising
29.4m old shares and the balance in new shares from January's rights issue,
at a price of 55 3/4 p. The old shares were then placed at 56 1/2 p.
Because of the difference between the old and new shares, the former being
entitled to a 0.1p dividend, De Zoete is understood not to have placed the
new shares to avoid confusion.
However, it is believed to have hedged its position in the remaining new
shares by selling short.
Spring Ram old shares fell 2p to 59p with volume recorded at 63.9m shares,
reflecting both the purchase and placing. The new shares were down 2p at
61p, with volume of 4.93m shares.
