FT  09 APR 94 / Letters to the Editor: No blame
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr MIKE JERAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I agreed with many of the points made by Sue Fernie and David Metcalf
about human resource management techniques (Recruitment, April 6, UK
edition; April 8, international). But they were unfair to lay most of the
blame on personnel specialists for HRM's failure to deliver its promises.
In my experience senior executives and managers generally have
enthusiastically endorsed HRM as part of a 'mission' to change
organisational culture rather than to improve employee relations or customer
service. Perhaps the situation would not be as bad as they describe if more
attention were paid to the views of staff and their representatives and
customers than to trendy management theories.
Mike Jeram,
