FT  08 APR 94 / International Company News: RJR Nabisco to pay off debt
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
RJR Nabisco, the US tobacco and foods group, is to pay off most of its
Dollars 2bn worth of subordinated debentures on May 15 using a combination
of fresh bank loans and cash, the company said yesterday, writes Richard
Tomkins in New York. The debt carries an average interest rate of 15 per
cent. RJR Nabisco said it was being paid off at the earliest possible
redemption date as part of its continuing programme of replacing expensive
borrowings with cheaper debt.
